  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are rallying on Middle East ceasefire hopes with equities extending winning streaks and oil pulling back from $100+ levels, while crypto sees strong momentum with Bitcoin approaching $73K and ETH eyeing $2.5K. However, weak US GDP data and concerning economic fundamentals suggest this remains a relief rally within the broader bear market regime. The fragile geopolitical situation and potential tariff deadline April 2nd keep volatility elevated.",
    "regimeImpact": "The bear market relief rally assessment remains intact as oil retreated from the critical $100 stagflation level and ceasefire hopes are providing temporary risk-on sentiment, but underlying economic weakness persists.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Continue BMNR cash-secured put ladder as Bitcoin approaches $73K resistance with whale selling activity suggesting potential pullback opportunity",
      "Maintain short book exposure as equities rally appears driven by temporary geopolitical relief rather than fundamental improvement",
      "Hold Maturity sector overweight given weak GDP growth and potential for defensive rotation if Middle East tensions re-escalate"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil pulled back from $100 stagflation threshold on ceasefire hopes, reducing immediate bear market catalyst",
      "Bitcoin whale selling of $271M suggests distribution near $73K resistance levels",
      "US GDP nowcast unchanged at 1.3% confirms economic weakness despite market rally",
      "Individual investor bears still 'unusually high' per AAII, supporting contrarian relief rally thesis"
    ]
